gov.usgs.quakeml.parser

Class QuakeMLHelper

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.usgs.quakeml.parser.QuakeMLHelper
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    GSE2_1

    public abstract class QuakeMLHelper
extends java.lang.Object
    This attempts to organize the various common bulletin elements into calls for each major element so logic that would be common to many bulletin translations can be put in one place Normal ordering : 1) Create a QuakeMLHelper generally through the format specific subclass, 2) addEventParameters() - make QML document for this event, adds author/creator infor 3) addEvent() - add an event to this QuakeML document (it might be a catalog of events) 4) addPicks() - like addGSEPick() 5) addMagnitude - add one or more magnitudes to the QuakeML 6) addOrigin - add one or more origins to the EventParameters 7) call writeEventXML() to create a file with the XML It includes many helper static methods for dealling with makeRealQuantity with various scales and uncertainties to cut down on the excessive decimal places that default realQuantities display with.

      • addEventParameters

        public void addEventParameters(java.lang.String publicID,
                               java.lang.String desc,
                               java.lang.String comment,
                               CreationInfo creInfo)
        This is the first all, it creates the QuakeML object, the EventParmeters object, adds the EventParamters to the QuakeML object, sets the EventParameters publicID. So to create a bulletin, call this once, and keep adding Events. To make individual QuakeML files, call this before each event add. The public iD is the $publicIDStub/eventparms/$filename/$publicID where the publicIDStub and filename were set when this object was created.
        Parameters:
        publicID - The public ID string, will be added to the parameters public id
        desc - A descriptive string
        comment - Any comment as a string
        creInfo - Creation information (agency ID, agencyURI, author, authorURI,creation time and version)

      • addEvent

        public Event addEvent(java.lang.String eventID)
        Add an event and make it the current one (the one picks, magnitudes, origins are added to) The publicID for the event is $publiIDStub/event/$eventID where publicIDStub came from the creation of this object.

        This sets up our copy of <List> of the magnitudes, amplitudes, origins, picks, stationMagnitude, and focalMechanisms. Note that means that as each event is "added" it become the current event for all of these items to be added via the add???() methods. So if there are multiple events for an object, all processing for each event must occur before the next call to addEvent().

        Parameters:
        eventID - The event ID string, will become the QML Event.eventID
        Returns:
        The created Event object

      • addOrigin

        protected GSOrigin addOrigin(java.lang.String publicID,
                             java.lang.String originID,
                             TimeQuantity time,
                             RealQuantity longitude,
                             RealQuantity latitude,
                             RealQuantity depth,
                             OriginDepthType depthType,
                             int timeFixed,
                             int epicenterFixed,
                             java.lang.String referenceSystemID,
                             java.lang.String methodID,
                             java.lang.String earthModel,
                             CompositeTime compositeTime,
                             OriginQuality originQuality,
                             OriginUncertainty originUncertainty,
                             OriginType originType,
                             java.lang.String region,
                             EvaluationMode evaluationMode,
                             EvaluationStatus evaluationStatus,
                             Comment comment,
                             CreationInfo creationInfo)
        Parameters:
        publicID - The id string (becomes a ResourceReference resourceID string), if null, publicIDStub+/origin/$originID
        originID - Some unique ID from creator of this origin
        time - GSOrigin time
        longitude - In degrees with negative in western hemisphere from zero meridian
        latitude - In degrees from equator, negative is south of equator
        depth - In meters
        depthType - from enum {FROM_LOCATION,FROM_MOMENT_TENSOR,BROADBAND_P_WAVEFORMS,CONSTRAINED_BY_DEPTH_PHASES,CONSTRAINED_BY_DIRECT_PHASES,OPERATOR_ASSIGNED,OTHER_ORIGIN_DEPTH}
        timeFixed - -1 if unknown, 0 if fixed, 1 if fixed origin time was used
        epicenterFixed - if -1 unknown, if 1 the epicenter was fixed, if zero it was unfixed
        referenceSystemID - A resourceID string (if null this will be properties publicIDStub+referenceSystemID
        methodID - A ResourceID string (if null this will be properties publicIDStub+originMethodid
        earthModel - A ResourceID string (if null, this will be properties publicIDStub+earthModelID
        compositeTime - Used for complex time of rupture
        originQuality - an origin quality object
        originUncertainty - An origin uncertainty object
        originType - from enum {HYPOCENTER,CENTROID,AMPLITUDE,MACROSEISMIC,RUPTURE_START,RUPTURE_END}
        region -
        evaluationMode - from enum {MANUAL, AUTOMATIC}
        evaluationStatus - from enum {PRELIMINARY,CONFIRMED,REVIEWED,FINAL,REJECTED}
        comment -
        creationInfo - Use this if it should not inherit from the event.
        Returns:
        The created GSOrigin object (inherits from QuakeML origin)

      • addStationMagnitude

        public void addStationMagnitude(GSArrival arrival,
                                java.lang.String mtype,
                                double mag,
                                java.lang.String arrID,
                                java.lang.String staMagID)
        If a GSE2.1 has a line with additional magnitude and mag type and arrival ID, add the StationMagnitudeContribution and StationMagnitude object and relate them to all of the required places (magnitude, Event, Origin, Amplitude)
        Parameters:
        arrival - The GSArrival object returned by the first full line for this phase
        mtype - The magnitude type as a string
        mag - The magnitude numeric value
        arrID - The arrival
        staMagID - ID from the GSE line

      • addAmp

        public void addAmp(GSArrival arr,
                   GSOrigin org,
                   java.lang.String arrID,
                   java.lang.String ampID,
                   double ampNM,
                   double per,
                   double snr,
                   java.lang.String mtype,
                   double mag,
                   java.lang.String staMagID,
                   java.lang.String seedname,
                   EvaluationMode emode,
                   EvaluationStatus estat)
        Parameters:
        arr - A GSArrival gotten from addArrival
        org - A GSOrigin returned by addOrigin
        arrID - The unique number to put on this arrival
        ampID - The publicID for this amplitude, if null, publicIDStub/amp/arrID will be used.
        ampNM - The amplitude in NANOMETERS
        per - Period in seconds
        snr - Signal to noise ration
        mtype - This must match the one used to create the magnitude record for this pick
        mag - The magnitude value from this amplitude for the stationMagnitude portion
        staMagID - The stationMagnitude publicID, if null, then publicIDStub/statmag/arrID
        seedname - Tje seedname of this arrival
        emode - The EvaluationMode value (one of the predefined values in EvaluationMode)

        Parameters:
        event - An event object to add this arrival to

        pickPublicID - Public ID string (becomes a ResourceReference resourceID string)
        arrivalID - Not apparently used
        arrivalTime - The time associated with this arrival
        seedname - A NSCL
        filterID - A filter ID if known
        pickMethodID - A pick method ID if known

        backAzimuth - The back azimth in degress from north

        onset - A pickOnset object which contains from enum {POSITIVE, NEGATIVE, UNDECIDABLE} if known
        pickPhaseHint - A Phase object, if known with a standard phase string in it
        polarity - A PickPolarity object, if known with enum {POSITIVE, NEGATIVE, UNDECIDABLE}
        evalMode - An EvaluationMode object, if known, enum {MANUAL, AUTOMATIC}
        evalStatus - if Known, enum {PRELIMINARY, CONFIRMED, REVIEWED, FINAL, REJECTED}
        phase - A phase code which will be used to make a phaseHint Phase
        timeCorrection - Any time correction, if zero, non is put in the arrival
        azimuth - The azimuth to the quake in degrees
        distance - The distance to the quake in degrees
        timeResidual - The time residual, if <-1000, no residual @param slowne ssResidual If > -1000., set this residual
        backAzimuthResidual - if > -1000., set this residual
        timeUsed - If true, time was used in the event location
        slownessUsed - if true, slowness was used in event location
        backazimuthUsed - if true, backazimuth was used in event location
        weight - The weighting factor, if < 0., no weight is given @param earthModelI D Earth model ID if known
        preliminary - if true, this is a preliminary arrival
        arrivalComment - Analyst or machine comment about the arrival
        arrivalCreate - CreationInfo for the arrival
        pickComment - Analyst or machine comment about the pick
        pickCreate - CreationInfo for the pick

        The GSArrival created
